#Summary1=(human1) Lucy Pope of the class of '71 gives advice to future inhabitants of her dorm room in Abbey House, telling about life with her roommates and how it has hurt some of their grades, suggesting to be quiet and not to talk back to Mrs. G., to take care not to be caught by guards for studying after lights out, and not leaving windows open without a screen to avoid bees.

#Summary2=(claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022) In a letter from May 30th, Lucy Pope (class of '71) writes to future residents of her 4-room dorm at P.A., describing her roommates and their departures, offering advice about dealing with Mrs. G and study habits, and concluding with an offer to sell her Greek & Roman History notebook.

#Summary3=(gpt4o) In a letter dated May 30, Lucy Pope of the class of '71 shares her experiences living in a four-room dorm, giving advice on dealing with roommates and staff, studying discreetly, avoiding bee infestations, and hints at selling her Greek and Roman history notes, while expressing her hope to room in the French House next year despite disliking Mrs. Abbot.

#Summary4=(Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct) Lucy Pope from the class of '71 shares her experiences and tips for living in a four-room dorm at Penn State in 1971, discussing roommates, studying, and campus life.

#Summary5=(Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct) Lucy Poppe, a member of the class of '71, describes her experiences living in a 4-room in preparation school, detailing roommates, challenges, and tips for fellow students, while expressing her hope to join French House next year.
#Text=Dear 3 or 4 Roomers -
#Text=( class of '71 )
#Text=Tonight is Thursday , May 30th .
#Text=The time is 10:55 P.M , and I 'm tired as hell .
#Text=I spent the entire day at picnics + beach parties at P.A. , but I 'll try to make a little bit of sense .

#Text=My First experiance with the 4 - room ( as it was this yr. ) was meeting my ROOMATES RUTH RASER , SALLY BROWNING AND karen HO , FROM Schenectady N.Y. , MYSTIC CONN. and HONG - KONG respectively .
#Text=Things went on well for a while , but it takes some getting used to .

#Text=Then around November Ruth had to move to a single because of bad grades - that 's one thing about this room , it can really hurt your grades - she moved upstairs to the 3rd floor , where there are 3 singles so the four - room became a 3 room for a while , until January , when the 3rd floor was condemned by some shitty building inspector .
#Text=Dory Streett who had lived upstairs in a single became my new commate .
#Text=We 've all existed so far but we 've been damn lucky , and have also worked damned hard .
#Text=A few hints .
#Text=First of all do n't talk back to Mrs. G. and you 'll have a good year .
#Text=Adele , the maid , is so dumb that you 'll have loads of fun just giving her gas .
#Text=voices from the 4 - room carry a lot farther than you think - you can tell this by listening from the bathroom .
#Text=So be quiet , but do n't worry - Mrs. G never reports you to Core for being noisy or staying up , only for things like cutting Church or required crap .
#Text=Unless they take them out this summer , you will notice 2 hooks in the ceiling of the outer porch .
#Text=Sally + I , whose beds were out on the porch used them for hanging flashlights over our beds for studying ( just tie them to used nylons or SOMEthing )
#Text=IF you have A SMALL STUDY LAMP you DO N'T EVEN NEED TO WORRY ABOUT THIS .
#Text=THE ONLY DANGER ABOUT AFTER LIGHTS STUDYING IS BEING REPORTED BY THE VICTOR OR PINKERTON GUARDS WHO PATROL THE CAMPUS TO PROTECT US FROM " TOWNIES "
#Text=NEVER EVER LEAVE THE WINDOWS OPEN DURING SPRING TERM without SCREENS , or you 'll find a BEE 'S NEST IN YOUR BED LIKE SALLY DID THIS SPRING .

#Text=WELL , ONE of MY ROOMATES is BITCHING LIKE CRAZY 'CAUSE she 's " TIRED , " so I CA N'T GO ON MUCH LONGER - WE 'RE HAVING A PARTY IN HERE TOMORROW NIGHT ( The last night of school ) so I guess I should try to get to sleep tonight too .
#Text=so just remember to give this room all you can and remember that it ca n't be all that bad .
#Text=Have a great 4 - room experience and a fantastic prep year - it 's supposed to be the best year to have , so TAKE ADVANTAGE .
#Text=I 'M TRYING FOR FRENCH HOUSE NEXT YEAR , AND I HOPE I 'll make it , cause I hate ABBEY HOUSE .
#Text=( I ALSO HATE MRS. ABBOT , HOUSEMOTHER IN FRENCH HOUSE , BUT THAT 'S LIFE )
#Text=So , LIKE EVERYBODY SAYS , COME ON UP , AND VISIT , I 'M ROOMING with RUTH AGAIN
#Text=Luv ,
#Text=Lucy Pope
#Text=class of '71
#Text=P.S.
#Text=IF THINGS GET DESPERATE , I 'M WILLING TO SELL MY GREEK + ROMAN HISTORY NOTEBOOK CONTAINING SECTIONS AND MAPS + NOTES FOR A SUITABLE PRICE .
#Text=CONSIDER THIS OFFER LATER WHEN MISS MUCK DEMANDS 30 SECTIONS IN ONE NIGHT .
#Text=( I GOT AN A- and a B ! )
